The paper deals with random quadratic forms of stochastic processes, which are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses applications to randomized algorithms and approximate linear algebra, which fall under numerical analysis (cs.NA) and data structures (cs.DS).
